values.text: March being the third month of the year is moderate, with an average temperature of 25 degree celcius, and an average humidity of around 69%. I would suggest good storage of food items in dry and temperature controlled area, be aware of rats and mice infesting your beloved stocks dear foodie!

The monsoons are here mate! with an average temperature of 34 degree celcius and humidity of around 85%, you would want to check on your drainage systems to avoid water clogging. Check for mould and fungus growths, and for God's sake! don't forget to carry an umbrella.

April being the fourth month of the year is relatively hot, with an average temperature of 30 degree celcius, and an average humidity of around 46%. I would suggest using a proper cold storage with regular inspection and maintenance. A periodic disinfection would go a long way. Enjoy the Spring though!

With an average temperature of around 23 degree celcius and mean humidity at 71%, November is one fine month to enjoy the joys of life. Not to worry about your stock is what I'll suggest you. They're just fine. And remember, Nothing lasts forever, not even cold november rain!

We're almost there! hope the year is turning out to be really good for you. Average temperatures will swing in the range of 25 degree celcius, with average humidity around 70%. Let's prepare for the yulitide season and stock up really fast.

Now these are really hot months I believe! Temperatures will reach a staggering 38 degrees celcius with average humidity at 55%. Keep a fresh stock if possible and avoid over storing the units. Don't forget to hydrate yourself though.

I know it'll get hot out there! phew! average temperatures will soar to 35 degree celcius with average humidity dropping to 45%. Look after that cold storage of your's and apply sunscreen while you go out!

July being the sixth month of the year is also the hottest, with an average temperature of 35 degree celcius, and an average humidity of around 77%. I would suggest that you store only what's required and have a check on the power supply units, you don't wanna fall amidst a power cut!  Drink loads of water and apply sunscreen while out!

With the end of the year round the corner, I want to thank you for your perseverance and grit! kudos mate! I know that sales are high right now and you're in no mood to joke around, but its chilly out there mate! grab an overcoat, raise a toast, its that time of the year again. Jingle all the way Mate!
Temperatures are dropping I believe, with an average of around 29 degree celcius and humidity in the range of 86%. No worries in this month mate! just keep up the high spirits.

February is the second month of the year and is moderate, with an average temperature of 24 degree celcius, and an average humidity of around 71%. I would suggest good storage of food items in dry and temperature controlled area. Spring is knocking at your door! let the flowers bloom.

January being the first month of the year is relatively cold, with an average temperature of 22.5 degree celcius, and an average humidity of around 79%. I would suggest good storage of food items in dry and temperature controlled area, although there is almost no worries in January.
